We recommended and Management agreed to direct:

a.	The GSO/Municipal Treasurer to:

Prepare and submit duly accomplished RPCI upon the conduct of physical count on inventories by the Inventory Committee;

We recommended, and Management agreed that:
The Inventory Committee to immediately conduct physical count of Road Networks, and prepare the Physical Count of the Road Network System of the Municipality using the pro-forma schedule in Annex C of COA Circular 2015-008;
The Municipal Engineer in coordination with the Municipal Assessor to provide the Accountant and GSO with the complete description and cost segregation of road components including road lots, road pavement, drainage and slope protection structures and other miscellaneous structures;
The Municipal Accountant, GSO and Municipal Engineer to reconcile their records on Road Network System of the LGU against the Report on Physical Count of the Road Network System;
The Municipal Accountant to prepare LRNLC for each road network component, and prepare a separate disclosure in the notes to Financial Statements the recognized road networks; and
The Municipal GSO at the end or every accounting period to render a Report on LRN using the pro-forma schedule in Annex A and maintain a local road inventory, Road Map and complete Road Network PCs for all roads and its components.

Recommendations
We recommended, and Management agreed to direct:
The Municipal Engineer to provide the Accountant and GSO with the complete description and cost segregation of road components including road lots, road pavement, drainage and slope protection structures and other miscellaneous structures;
The Municipal Accountant to maintain complete LRN Ledger Card for each road network component;
The Inventory Committee to prepare the Physical Count of the Road Network System of the Municipality using the pro-forma schedule in Annex C of COA Circular 2015-008;
The Municipal GSO at the end or every accounting period to render a Report on Local Road Network using the pro-forma schedule in Annex A and maintain a local road inventory, Road Map and complete Road Network Property Card for all roads and its components; and
The Municipal Assessor to assist in assessing the fair value of road network assets acquired thru non-exchange transactions

7.11 We recommended that the Local Chief Executive direct the Municipal Treasurer and concerned officials agreed to:
7.11.1 to request checkbooks for the new LBP account and close old account to maintain only one (1) depository account with the Land Bank of the Philippines;
7.11.2 close the existing PNB Time deposit accounts in accordance with DOF Department Circular No. 001-2017 and transfer the same to LBP-Sindangan Branch, duly authorized and approved by the Sangguniang Bayan and Local Chief Executive, upon its maturity to avoid imposition of pre-termination fees and charges.

13.3 We recommended and the Management agreed to:
13.3.1 Require the personnel who is assigned in the control of the fuel to prepare and submit timely and regularly the Monthly Report of Fuel Consumption for CY 2021 and onwards summarizing all the issuances for the month supported with the duly issued and approved Gas Slip together with the Delivery Receipt issued by the gasoline station upon withdrawal, for approval of the GSO/Treasurer and the Local Chief Executive to diligently monitor the issuance thereof;
13.3.2 	Likewise, the payment of fuel is to be attached with the usual documents coming from the BAC depending on the acquisition modality together with the PO, Certificate of Deposit issued by the Gasoline station and such other documentary evidences since asset method is used in the accounting of its fuel procurement and/or delivery while the consumption is accounted for as an expense upon withdrawal from the gasoline station.

The Management direct the Accounting Office to properly recognize and present in the financial statements the cost and the respective accumulated depreciation of each component of the Local Road Networks, in compliance with Item IV-Accounting Policies of COA Circular No. 2015-008.

Furthermore, the Municipal Mayor, as provided by COA Circular No. 2015-008 dated November 25, 2015, require the coordination and cooperation of the following personnel:

a.   Local Accountant-
1.    Prepare the Journal Voucher to record the beginning balance of the road network and its components in the general ledger and the Local Road Networks Ledger Card (Annex D), respectively;

2.    Support the JEV with the Registry of Public Infrastructures for Roads, working paper on the distribution of costs for the road components, and working paper on the determination of the depreciated replacement cost for road components with no available cost per registry;

3.    Keep and maintain subsidiary records for roads and components for every road network; 

4.    Prepare a lapsing schedule for the computation of the depreciation for each component at the end of the year;

5.    Disclose the total road network of the Municipality in the Notes to the Financial Statements of the Agency (Annex B).

b. Municipal Treasurer/ General Services Officer
6.    Maintain a Local Road Inventory and Road Map; 

7.    Keep a complete Local Road Network Property Card for all roads and its components (Annex E).

8.    Render a Report on Local Road Network of the Municipality (Annex A).

c. Municipal Engineer 
9.    Provide the local accountant and the general services officer with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects.

d. Inventory Committee 
10. Prepare the Report on the Physical Count of the Road Network System of the Municipality (Annex C), in accordance with this circular.

