12.8 We recommended that the Management:
Direct the Accounting Unit to prepare the necessary adjusting entries to correct the overstatement of the Other Payables account by P8.23 million, understated amount of the Trust Liabilities - Disaster Risk Reduction and Management Fund by P6.44 million and the reversion to the Unappropriated surplus by P1.89 million; transfer the P1.84 million, which represents the unutilized portion of 30 per cent Quick Response Fund for CY 2019 to the Trust Fund;
Direct the members of the Municipal Disaster Risk Reduction and Management Council (MDRRMC) to ensure that the programs, projects and activities to be included in the Local Disaster Risk Reduction and Management Fund Investment Plan (LDRRMFIP) shall cover the priority LDRRMF projects and activities that are included or related to the DRRM activities as declared under Section 3.0 of COA Circular No. 2012-002. Be guided with the provisions of Section 5.0 of NDRRMC, DBM and DILG JMC No. 2013-01;
Initiate the creation of the four (4) statutory and mandatory DRRM positions composed of one (1) Local DRRM Officer and three (3) DRRM staff positions as required under Joint Memorandum Circular (JMC) No. 2014-1;
Provide for the amount and details discussing the unexpended balance of LDRRMF in the Notes to Financial Statements as required in Section 5.1.16 of COA Circular No. 2012-002;
Refrain from using the 30 per cent Quick Response Fund without the Local Sanggunian Resolution and the declaration of state of calamity; and
Direct the LDRRM Office to submit timely and consistently the Report on the Receipt and Utilization of DRRMF in compliance to the Reporting Guidelines of COA Circular 2014-002 dated April 15, 2014.
12.9 Management Comment:
Management was receptive to our recommendation and commit to implement as recommended.  The unexpended fund was already reprogrammed to calamity related priority PPAs per Resolution no. 01-S-2019.

We recommend that the Municipal Engineer undertake the following:
1.  Application of the asphalt sealant on the concrete pavements joints costing P15,000.00;
2.  Improvement of longitudinal cracks in pavements at Sta 0+000 - Sta 0 + 070 (30m) from Brgy. Isian Norte going to Sitio Lanag;
3.  Clearing of 0.50 meter of roadside shouldering that were already vegetated.

Refund of the amounts equivalent to the works not applied will be enforced.
